      serialVersionUID:
      -8866269808589635947L

      • Serialized Fields

        • isstop

          int isstop
          Gives the reason for termination. 1 means x is an approximate solution to Ax = b. 2 means x approximately solves the least-squares problem.

        • r1norn

          double r1norn
          Represents norm(r), where r = b - Ax.

        • r2norm

          double r2norm
          Represents sqrt( norm(r)^2 + damp^2 * norm(x)^2 ). Equal to r1norm if damp == 0.

        • anorm

          double anorm
          Estimate of Frobenius norm of Abar = [[A]; [damp*I]].

        • acond

          double acond
          Estimate of cond(Abar).

        • arnorm

          double arnorm
          Estimate of norm(A'*r - damp^2*x).

        • xnorm

          double xnorm
          Represents norm(x).

        • var

          double[] var
          If calc_var is True, estimates all diagonals of (A'A)^{-1} (if damp == 0) or more generally (A'A + damp^2*I)^{-1}. This is well defined if A has full column rank or damp > 0.

        • minImpurityIncreaseForRecord

          double minImpurityIncreaseForRecord
          In case of compression min impurity increase that will be recorded.

        • minImpurityDecreaseForRecord

          double minImpurityDecreaseForRecord
          In case of compression min impurity decrease that will be recorded.
